  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Approved. 49 vocab + 26 grammar (one rich directions/prepositions-of-place structure, 9 formats). Grants: turn/left/right/straight/ahead/corner/beside (SB directions box). This unit drove two systemic validator refinements (committed): V-8 now treats motion-verb/preposition/quantifier glue (go, on, most) as non-leaking in a multiword headword — defining \"to go past\" without \"go\" is impossible at A1 — while still flagging distinctive content (bus, train, lights); and V-9/V-17 distractor gating is now phrase-aware (a distractor sentence \"…at the traffic lights\" passes) and honors grants for vocab mc. Smoke-check fixed 5 circular direction-phrase definitions + a chip/carrier/label cluster. Verify round 1 caught two defensibly-correct distractors (behind in gf.001; \"at the corner of\" in gf.009, plus its explainDe wrongly calling \"at\" wrong) and one orphaned gloss I introduced (bus on bus-stop) — all fixed; round 2 clean. Stage-8: 6 glosses correct, 51 translations accurate (F58 \"weak evidence\" on to-go-past's German is a heuristic — vorbeigehen/vorbeigehen an/vorbei gehen are all correct). rejectRate 0.0%."
